		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Louis</placeName>&#44; <date>October 8&#44; 1866</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Very honored Sir&#58; I transmit &#36;50 to<lb/> you. Let me know whether you have received it.<lb/> I have not yet sold the Pentateuchs with English<lb/> translation&#44; either in the ordinary or fine<lb/> binding&#44; but I have orders from six men for<lb/> the same expensive Bibles as well as English<lb/> prayer books. I need Bibles that are bound like<lb/> the last ones I received&#44; and prayer books for<lb/> women by <persName>Heather Rothschild</persName>&#44; reprinted by you&#44; well&#45;<lb/>bound and with gilted locks. The former locks were very<lb/> poor. I had to sell them at a 50 cent loss.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please write to me by return mail the<lb/> price for medium and ordinary well&#45;bound<lb/> Bibles in English&#44; the so&#45;called parlor&#45;Bible <add>&#63;</add>.<lb/> I want to see&#44; then&#44; whether I could sell a<lb/> dozen. Write to me the price for freight if I<lb/> should have to pay it and still earn some&#45;<lb/> thing. That means three different prices.<lb/> The women&#39;s prayer books in English must be<lb/> very nicely bound with gilt locks. Please let<lb/> me know the price&#44; then I shall give you the<lb/> order.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If Hebrew Bibles cannot be sold&#44; the<lb/> Jews should buy English ones. &#8220;That it<lb/> should not be forgotten among his seed.&#8221;<lb/> I am looking for your immediate response. I<lb/> still feel weak after my sickness. The hand still<lb/> trembles. My congregation gave me a gift of &#36;300<lb/> for <date>Rosh Hashonah</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Your Friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">H. Kuttner</persName></p>
				<p>The city number has been changed. My<lb/> address is <persName role="author">Rev. H. Kuttner</persName>. <placeName>Box No 804&#44;North 10th St. Between Mason<lb/> and Franklin Avenue</placeName>.</p>
		</body>
